lutions that acknowledge and account for this. The volume also features commentaries and insights from other renowned economists, including an introduction by Joseph P. Newhouse that provides context for the discussion, a commentary from Jonathan Gruber that considers provider-side moral hazard, and reflections from Joseph E. Stiglitz and Kenneth J. Arrow.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aHealth insurance. 0aMoral hazard. 0aRisk (Insurance) 0aRisk (Insurance). 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economic History.2bisacsh1 aArrow, Kenneth J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArrow, Kenneth.1 aFinkelstein, Amy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGruber, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGruber, Jonathan.1 aNewhouse, Joseph P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewhouse, Joseph.1 aStiglitz, Joseph E.1 aStiglitz, Joseph E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311066586440uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/fink1638040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231538688423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231538688.jpg  a978-3-11-066586-4  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK